<p>Since there is exactly one integer in a <a href="/wiki/Half-open_interval" class="mw-redirect" title="Half-open interval">half-open interval</a> of length one, for any real number <i>x</i>, there are unique integers <i>m</i> and <i>n</i> satisfying the equation
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle x-1&lt;m\leq x\leq n&lt;x+1.}">
